1
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:40,820
=Visage and Soul=

2
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:43,040
(The "Different Her"
Trilogy on Women's Relationships)

3
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,640
=Episode 4=

4
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,440
What bad luck.

5
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,240
Qiao Zhiwei,

6
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:04,320
was Ye Xiaoduo really our sister?

7
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:11,680
I'm curious.

8
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,640
Do you want her to be,

9
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,160
or not?

10
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,920
I know she was Dad's
illegitimate daughter.

11
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:24,240
But why did no one ever talk about her?

12
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,280
Not you, and not Dad either.

13
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,280
Didn't you just say

14
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,280
she was illegitimate?

15
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:33,640
Keeping her hidden
isn't exactly surprising.

16
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,960
Were we ever mean to her?

17
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,840
Listen to yourself.

18
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:41,200
An older brother and sister

19
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,160
playing with their younger sister.

20
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,920
How is that being mean?

21
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,200
Especially you. As her big sister,

22
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:52,360
you loved playing with her the most

23
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:54,440
your special game.

24
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:56,960
What are you talking about?

25
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,520
You don't remember?

26
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,720
Your favorite special game.

27
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,200
What are you doing?

28
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:29,600
When you come home, could you

29
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,200
just stay in your little corner?

30
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:34,040
Stop wandering around here
and being an eyesore.

31
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:35,720
Give it back!

32
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,160
Cheap stuff is cheap.

33
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,920
What kind of junk is this?

34
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,360
It's not junk.

35
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,800
My mom made it for me by hand.

36
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,080
Didn't your mom make things for you too?

37
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,400
So you're jealous?

38
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,720
Jealous?

39
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,600
I'm jealous of you?

40
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,400
My silly little sister,

41
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,480
can't you tell what she's really saying?

42
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:06,280
She's mocking you for being motherless.

43
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:20,120
You can't let
this illegitimate girl beat you.

44
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:23,280
Otherwise, Dad will like her even more.

45
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,280
Say that again.

46
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,520
Say that again!

47
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,960
What are you staring at?

48
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,640
You got a problem?

49
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,480
I honestly don't get it.

50
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,040
Why do girls like you,
illegitimate daughters,

51
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,680
always so defiant?

52
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,400
Give it back.

53
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,880
Qiao Zhiwei!

54
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:55,720
Apologize.

55
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,520
How dare you raise
a hand to your sister?

56
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,480
Where are your manners?

57
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:07,840
Is that how your mother raised you?

58
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,000
Don't push me.

59
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,040
Or none of us will have a good time.

60
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,720
Just wait.

61
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,160
Did you remember something?

62
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,440
Back then,

63
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,080
I was the only one

64
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:36,200
who truly looked out for you.

65
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,920
Ye Xiaoduo had already lost her mother.

66
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,080
Why did you still bully her?

67
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,640
She's already dead.

68
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,080
Who are you saying all this for?

69
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,440
I'm all the family you have left.

70
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,000
Try being a little nicer to me.

71
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,720
And don't forget

72
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,920
my allowance from the old man.

73
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,440
First tell me how Ye Xiaoduo died.

74
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,200
Her?

75
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,760
She died because she was stupid.

76
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,760
Tell me, and I'll send
the money right away.

77
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,960
Sometimes fate really isn't fair.

78
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,120
One fire,

79
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:28,400
and some people die in the flames.

80
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,840
While others

81
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,200
inherit a fortune worth billions.

82
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,120
So...

83
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,280
that fire...

84
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,280
Ye Xiaoduo really started it?

85
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,160
What else would it be?

86
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,480
But Dad said it was an accident.

87
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,920
You're funny.

88
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,760
You were there.

89
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,240
And you're asking me?

90
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,440
Then why

91
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,880
wouldn't Dad let me be with Qin Yu?

92
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,560
Because he's a liar.

93
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,320
He said he could paint.

94
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:04,240
He said

95
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,360
you were the only one he'd ever love.

96
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,960
Too bad.

97
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,800
They were all lies.

98
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:17,320
Losing your memory
is a blessing, Xiaomi.

99
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,560
If

100
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,680
you really remembered your old self,

101
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,200
you might end up hating who you are now.

102
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,720
Enjoy the good life you have now.

103
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,160
And don't forget my allowance.

104
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:08,360
(Feb 15, 2023) (A faceless man appears.)
Because he's a liar.

105
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,280
(Feb 15, 2023) (A faceless man appears.)
He said

106
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,480
you were the only one he'd ever love.

107
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,520
(Jul 7, 2022) (A girl was in my dream.)
The fire you survived

108
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,520
is the same fire that killed her.

109
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:17,370
(Mar 26, 2024)

110
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,320
(Mar 26, 2024) (An easel in my memory.)
Xiaomi.

111
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:19,520
(Mar 26, 2024) (An easel in my memory.)
I've come back to marry you.

112
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,360
I'm your fiancé.

113
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,280
It's been three years.

114
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,160
I've missed you every single day.

115
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,400
Too bad.

116
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,240
They were all lies.

117
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:31,870
(Qin Yu, a liar?)

118
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,600
Ye Xiaoduo.

119
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,000
The fire.

120
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,120
Qin Yu.

121
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,480
Ye Xiaoduo is dead.

122
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,360
I've lost my memory.

123
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,040
Qin Yu vanished, then came back.

124
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,160
None of this can be a coincidence.

125
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,400
Qin Yu...

126
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:54,560
Why exactly did he come back?

127
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,000
Miss Qiao,

128
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,680
it took me a lot of effort

129
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:05,080
to acquire this painting
from a collector.

130
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,120
As for the style,

131
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,360
it perfectly matches

132
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,200
the style Mr. Qiao loved most.

133
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,520
Just look at the texture.

134
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:14,000
It fits perfectly
with your gallery's style.

135
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,680
Qin Yu, are you insane?

136
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,680
Who are you?

137
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,560
Are you crazy?

138
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:31,640
This painting...

139
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,040
It's worth millions!

140
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,560
Worth millions?

141
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,240
Do you really think

142
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,880
there's no one in this family
who knows art?

143
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,760
Or do you think
my fiancée is an easy target?

144
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,960
Caravaggio-style chiaroscuro,

145
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:52,040
yet it uses cadmium red,
a pigment made in the 19th century.

146
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,520
This isn't a forgery.

147
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,240
It's an insult to art history.

148
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,440
Y-You're talking nonsense!

149
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:03,360
This painting comes
with authentication papers!

150
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,640
With genuine old paintings,

151
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:08,560
the pigments seep
into the canvas itself.

152
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,400
But in this one,

153
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,280
the paint sits on the surface.

154
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:14,280
Would you like me

155
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,280
to call the authorities right now

156
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,920
and have them take a look

157
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,200
at your so-called
million-yuan masterpiece?

158
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,920
Before the force arrives,

159
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:33,400
the intent leads.

160
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,000
Go with the flow.

161
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,200
Borrow the force.

162
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,200
Redirect the force.

163
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:41,880
What's that?

164
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,200
Who's talking?

165
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:51,640
Are you okay?

166
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,400
You're a grown man.
Is it really that serious?

167
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,240
How about I take you to the hospital?

168
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,680
What's wrong with me isn't physical.

169
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,640
A hospital can't fix it.

170
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,120
I sent you the medical bill.

171
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:40,960
Go by yourself.

172
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,440
What do you take me for?

173
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,040
You went to all that trouble

174
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,040
to show up at my father's funeral.

175
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:59,280
And time after time,
you've come to my rescue.

176
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,800
Isn't it all for our family's money?

177
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,320
Even if

178
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,320
I wanted your family's money,

179
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:23,160
do you really think

180
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:25,320
a 200-yuan cash gift
would be enough to get rid of me?

181
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,640
Then how much do you want?

182
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,440
Name your price.

183
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:54,320
The only thing I've ever wanted

184
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,000
is for you to remember me.

185
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,230
♪We say good morning,
we say good night♪

186
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:43,650
♪We say we miss each other,
but never speak of the hurt♪

187
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:47,140
♪The sweeter it is,
the luckier we seem♪

188
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:51,130
♪Yet the more romantic,
the rougher the road♪

189
00:12:52,370 --> 00:12:54,230
♪Let me go, set me free♪

190
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:58,270
♪Let me drown in reckless silence♪

191
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:04,220
♪We were perfect for each other,
yet you never admitted it♪

192
00:13:05,570 --> 00:13:07,710
♪The freedom you gave me♪

193
00:13:07,710 --> 00:13:11,350
♪Became the heaviest chain I bear♪

194
00:13:12,610 --> 00:13:14,880
♪Love can barely move forward♪

195
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:18,660
♪Yet the words still linger unspoken♪

196
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:22,000
♪The closeness I long for♪

197
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:26,390
♪There's no need for you
to keep avoiding it♪

198
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:28,620
♪I don't want to break free♪

199
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:33,990
♪Take back the chains
disguised as freedom♪

